+[{"id":"C-00-political-context-001","u":"00-political-context.html","t":"The second-term Trump administration is pressuring all three at once. It is attacking federal DEI infrastructure, leaning into tariffs and onshoring, pressuring climate-finance alignments, and backing legal and political attacks on collusive censorship systems.","ec":3,"d":"","ti":"","tg":[]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-001","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"Pew Research reported in May 2025 that 45% of White adults said White people face at least some discrimination, compared with 27% of Hispanic adults, 24% of Black adults, and 20% of Asian adults; Republicans were also far more likely than Democrats to say White people face discrimination, 55% versus 21%.","ec":2,"d":"2025-05-20","ti":"Pew found White adults far more likely than other groups to say White people face discrimination","tg":["pew","discrimination","white","polarization"]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-002","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"Pew also reported in May 2025 that 57% of Americans said religious people face at least some discrimination, while 57% of Republicans and 31% of Democrats said evangelical Christians face at least some discrimination.","ec":1,"d":"2025-05-20","ti":"Pew recorded substantial perceived discrimination against religious people and evangelicals","tg":["pew","religion","evangelicals","discrimination"]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-003","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"The Human Rights Campaign's 2025 Corporate Equality Index criteria explicitly awarded points for sexual-orientation and gender-identity protections, same-sex domestic-partner parity, transgender-inclusive health coverage, pronoun-sharing policies, LGBTQ+ employee groups, LGBTQ+ supplier diversity, LGBTQ+ marketing, and demonstrated public advocacy.","ec":1,"d":"2025-01-01","ti":"HRC CEI criteria operationalized protected-identity compliance inside firms","tg":["hrc","cei","lgbt","compliance","corporations"]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-004","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"The Human Rights Campaign's 2026 CEI reporting page said Fortune 500 participation fell by 65%, from 377 companies in 2025 to 131 in 2026, which shows both that the architecture was real and that retreat from it became measurable under pressure.","ec":1,"d":"2026-01-01","ti":"HRC reported a 65 percent collapse in Fortune 500 participation","tg":["hrc","cei","retreat","corporations"]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-005","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"The UN Standards of Conduct for Business and the WEF-linked Partnership for Global LGBTI Equality both pushed firms beyond internal HR policy and toward public advocacy and supply-chain enforcement.","ec":2,"d":"2026-01-01","ti":"OHCHR and WEF-linked initiatives treated identity compliance as business governance","tg":["ohchr","wef","pgle","business","governance"]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-006","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"The demographic side belongs here too because the agenda paper ties cultural subversion to weakened continuity. Statistics Canada reported a record-low total fertility rate of 1.25 in 2024 and a record maternal age of 31.8 years; it also later reported that 51.5% of women age 20 to 49 had no children in 2024 and that Canadian-born women in that age range were less likely to have children than landed immigrant women.","ec":2,"d":"2025-09-24","ti":"Canada's fertility record moved in the same direction as the broader continuity argument","tg":["fertility","canada","demographics","continuity"]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-007","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"Gallup reported in October 2025 that trust in newspapers, television, and radio to report the news fully, accurately, and fairly fell to 28%, the first time the measure had dropped below 30%.","ec":1,"d":"2025-10-02","ti":"Gallup recorded trust in media at a record low","tg":["gallup","media","trust"]},{"id":"C-01-system-logic-008","u":"01-system-logic.html","t":"FIRE reported in January 2026 that its Scholars Under Fire database logged 525 sanction attempts against faculty in 2025, with 460 resulting in some form of punishment, including 29 firings.","ec":1,"d":"2026-01-06","ti":"FIRE recorded record faculty-sanction activity in 2025","tg":["fire","academia","sanctions","censorship"]},{"id":"C-02-elite-factions-001","u":"02-elite-factions.html","t":"The World Economic Forum's own governance pages identify Larry Fink as Interim Co-Chair of the Forum, which is one of the clearest documented overlaps between the WEF governance layer and the BlackRock ownership layer.","ec":3,"d":"2026-02-26","ti":"Larry Fink is listed as WEF interim co-chair","tg":["wef","larry-fink","blackrock","governance"]},{"id":"C-03-ownership-layer-001","u":"03-ownership-layer.html","t":"The Big Three in this dossier means **BlackRock, Vanguard, and State Street**. They repeatedly appear as major institutional holders across large public companies, including major media parents.","ec":4,"d":"","ti":"","tg":[]},{"id":"C-03-ownership-layer-002","u":"03-ownership-layer.html","t":"Each of those companies can be audited through SEC proxy statements and 13G filings, where the Big Three repeatedly show up as major institutional holders.","ec":5,"d":"","ti":"Major media parents can be checked directly through SEC ownership disclosures","tg":["sec","media","ownership","big-three"]},{"id":"C-03-ownership-layer-003","u":"03-ownership-layer.html","t":"Fox is the best reminder that ownership influence is not the same thing as direct command. The Murdoch structure preserves control through dual-class shares even while large institutions still hold major economic stakes.","ec":2,"d":"","ti":"Dual-class shares can preserve control even with large institutional ownership","tg":["fox","murdoch","control","governance"]},{"id":"C-04-compliance-network-001","u":"04-compliance-network.html","t":"The Trusted News Initiative is one of the cleanest coordination nodes because it was publicly described as a cross-organization partnership targeting election