y emphasis","tg":["nashville","trans","media","asymmetry"]},{"id":"C-05-manufactured-outrage-007","u":"05-manufactured-outrage.html","t":"Rolling Stone's UVA rape story and the Duke lacrosse case both showed how moral panic, institutional appetite, and media appetite can outrun basic verification and leave innocent targets carrying the social stain long after collapse.","ec":2,"d":"","ti":"UVA and Duke remain two of the cleanest journalistic-moral-panic receipts","tg":["uva","duke","rape-hoax","media"]},{"id":"C-05-manufactured-outrage-008","u":"05-manufactured-outrage.html","t":"In Canada, the Toronto hijab-cutting hoax and the residential-school mass-graves story both functioned as high-speed moral weapons before scrutiny caught up.","ec":3,"d":"","ti":"Canadian examples show the same speed-versus-verification failure mode","tg":["canada","hijab-hoax","residential-schools","media"]},{"id":"C-05-manufactured-outrage-009","u":"05-manufactured-outrage.html","t":"The Alexis Jay inquiry into Rotherham estimated that approximately 1,400 children were sexually exploited between 1997 and 2013 and explicitly set out to examine whether agencies failed to act because of concerns about racial or ethnic sensitivities.","ec":2,"d":"","ti":"The Rotherham inquiry itself built racial-sensitivity concerns into the accountability question","tg":["rotherham","alexis-jay","child-exploitation","racial-sensitivity"]},{"id":"C-05-manufactured-outrage-010","u":"05-manufactured-outrage.html","t":"Baroness Casey's 2025 national audit on group-based child sexual exploitation said there was an appalling lack of ethnicity data, that the role of ethnicity and culture had to be examined, and that transparency on offender characteristics was necessary rather than racist.","ec":2,"d":"2025-06-16","ti":"The Casey audit directly challenged the fear-based suppression of offender-ethnicity questions","tg":["casey-review","grooming-gangs","ethnicity","transparency"]},{"id":"C-06-protected-categories-00