n instead of pure leverage","tg":["canada","tariffs","inflation","bank-of-canada"]},{"id":"C-09-trade-canada-003","u":"09-trade-canada.html","t":"The White House's April 2, 2025 framework continued 0% treatment for USMCA-compliant goods from Canada and Mexico, which meant Ottawa still had a path to preserve access instead of escalating by reflex.","ec":1,"d":"","ti":"USMCA-compliant access still existed under the April 2025 framework","tg":["usmca","tariffs","canada","white-house"]},{"id":"C-10-second-term-pressure-points-001","u":"10-second-term-pressure-points.html","t":"First, DEI. Federal DEI expansion stopped being a one-way ratchet and turned into a live legal and administrative fight.","ec":1,"d":"","ti":"","tg":[]},{"id":"C-10-second-term-pressure-points-002","u":"10-second-term-pressure-points.html","t":"Second, climate and energy. The administration is pushing fossil approvals, emergency framing, and rollback pressure against the net-zero governance model.","ec":1,"d":"","ti":"","tg":[]},{"id":"C-10-second-term-pressure-points-003","u":"10-second-term-pressure-points.html","t":"Third, trade. Tariffs are being used as leverage to punish offshoring, force concessions, and reprice access to the U.S. market.","ec":1,"d":"","ti":"","tg":[]},{"id":"C-10-second-term-pressure-points-004","u":"10-second-term-pressure-points.html","t":"Fourth, the compliance network. The TNI-related antitrust intervention matters because it signals that viewpoint collusion can be treated as a legal problem rather than a noble exception.","ec":1,"d":"","ti":"","tg":[]},{"id":"C-10-second-term-pressure-points-005","u":"10-second-term-pressure-points.html","t":"DHS repeatedly said assaults on ICE officers surged in 2025, moving from 413% to 500%, then 830%, and later more than 1000% in official department messaging as the year went on.","ec":4,"d":"","ti":"DHS publicly tied a steep assault spike to the broader demonization of ICE","tg":["ice","assaults","dhs","rhetoric"]},{"id":"C-10-s